    "description":"Black and white photographic image showing a huge motorcycle wheel in left foreground, and a smaller image of a young boy running (seen from behind), in the lower right corner. In order to promote traffic safety, the poster is designed so the vehicle tire threateningly appears to be about to run over the child.  Text in red Akzidenz Grotesk type face at upper left:  Automobil-Club der Schweiz (Automobile Club of Switzerland); below in white Akizidence Grotesk: \" Sch\u00fczt das Kind!\"  Yellow ground across bottom edge.  This poster is the designer's earliest use of the graphic design technique of photo-montage.  It also is constructed on the basis of a grid system (see Notes).",
